      "writtenOn": "2019-11-11T19:26:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think it should be \"if a test variant has any unexpected results\", so that  this filter will be helpful for getting both failed and flaky results.\n\nActually, I would prefer having ExpectancyFilter as:\n\n- ALL\n\n// TV with only unexpected failures, this is useful to present failed results.\n- VARIANTS_WITH_ONLY_UNEXPECTED_FAILURES \n\n// TV with only unexpected results (including unexpected successes). I don\u0027t know if there\u0027s a valid use case for it so far. So probably we don\u0027t need it.\n- VARIANTS_WITH_ONLY_UNEXPECTED_RESULTS\n\n// TV with any unexpected failures. This will helpful to present potentially flaky results.\n- VARIANTS_WITH_ANY_UNEXPECTED_FAILURES\n\nI don\u0027t know if there\u0027s a valid use case for UNEXPECTED_RESULTS, so I don\u0027t include it in the above list.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 54,
        "startChar": 36,
        "endLine": 55,
        "endChar": 29
      },
      "revId": "e0dec1671bf9efd701d41170a91ba9492a61f6fa",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9ad51fd4_e4a58ebd",
        "filename": "resultdb/proto/rpc/v1/query.proto",
