      "writtenOn": "2019-11-12T00:11:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "this was just an example for illustration. The definition is the first sentence that says what you are saying, essentially. I\u0027ve rephrased this.\n\nre your proposal:\n1) what is the use case for filtering by status, in addition to filtering by whether result is expected?\n2) your proposed schema mixes predicate-by-expectency and predicate-by-status into one, resulting in combinatorial explosion of options. Wouldn\u0027t it be better to have two separate predicates, the one that is in PS6 and, if we really need, a list of testStatuses?",
      "parentUuid": "9ee794b6_e70e20d1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 54,
        "startChar": 36,
        "endLine": 55,
        "endChar": 29
      },
      "revId": "e0dec1671bf9efd701d41170a91ba9492a61f6fa",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
