      "writtenOn": "2019-11-12T20:41:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e this was just an example for illustration. The definition is the first sentence that says what you are saying, essentially. I\u0027ve rephrased this. \n\nAh, indeed.\n\n\u003e re your proposal:\n\u003e 1) what is the use case for filtering by status, in addition to filtering by whether result is expected?\n\nAFAIR, many systems only concern about unexpected failures (Flake portal is a case, and I vaguely remember recipes is too). So if a test is expected to Fail and it unexpectedly passes, the systems don\u0027t care.\n\n\n\n\u003e 2) your proposed schema mixes predicate-by-expectency and predicate-by-status into one, resulting in combinatorial explosion of options. Wouldn\u0027t it be better to have two separate predicates, the one that is in PS6 and, if we really need, a list of testStatuses?\n\nYeah, that sounds good.",
      "parentUuid": "9ad51fd4_e4a58ebd",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 54,
        "startChar": 36,
        "endLine": 55,
        "endChar": 29
      },
      "revId": "e0dec1671bf9efd701d41170a91ba9492a61f6fa",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
